"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-16-paris-2024-olympics-nigerias-dismal-performance-worries-enthusiasts\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  on  By  Few days after the conclusion of the 2024 Olympic Games, sports loving Nigerians are still reeling with disappointment following the country's dismal showing.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nigeria went to Paris 2024 with 88 athletes and took part in 12 sporting events.\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 195, \"end\": 205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2876632987509484e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much was expected from the likes of Tobi Amusan, Ese Brume, Blessing Oborodudu and other top athletes but the country returned home without a single medal.\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 297, \"end\": 308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oluwatobiloba_Amusan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tobi Amusan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oluwatobiloba_Amusan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oluwatobiloba_Amusan\"}, {\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ese_Brume\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ese Brume\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ese_Brume\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ese_Brume\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amusan is the current world record holder in the women's 100m hurdles.\", \"from\": 418, \"to\": 488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old, who finished fourth in the same event three years ago in Tokyo, was in fine form heading to Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997396679077224, \"rank\": 0.00026039819672951653, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 599, \"end\": 609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2876632987509484e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Commonwealth and African champion, however, failed to make it to the final, finishing third in the semi-final.\", \"from\": 612, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2693932361189987e-11, \"text\": \"Commonwealth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brume, a bronze medallist three years ago in Tokyo also failed to fulfill expectations, finishing fifth in the women's long jump final.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997396679077224, \"rank\": 0.00026039819672951653, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another medalist (silver) from Tokyo, Blessing Oborodudu came close to winning a medal but was hampered by injury.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 896, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997396679077224, \"rank\": 0.00026039819672951653, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other medal hopefuls, Favour Ofili, Odunayo Adekuroye and Chidi Okezie failed to deliver the goods.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1003, \"end\": 1015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Favour_Ofili\", \"score\": 0.9999688897388217, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Favour Ofili\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Favour_Ofili\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Favour_Ofili\"}, {\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chidi_Okezie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chidi Okezie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chidi_Okezie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chidi_Okezie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the only bright spot was Nigeria's women's basketball team, D'Tigress.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1115, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998226030742, \"rank\": 1.773969165549162e-07, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1150, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"D'Tigress\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The African champions, against expectations, made it to the quarter-finals in the event, beating world number three and five (Australia and Canada) in the group stage.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.6680216550686066, \"rank\": 0.46757722285837056, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.7513130664430849, \"rank\": 0.2936836343058719, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"D'Tigress succumbed gallantly to holders United States of America in the last eight.\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where the country got it wrong  The blame game is already on following the conclusion of hostilities in Paris.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998908606, \"rank\": 1.0931179370576646e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The questions many are asking is what are the reasons behind the country's poor showing?\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why did the likes of Amusan, Brume, and Oborodudu fail to fulfill expectations?\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Did the sports ministry provide enough funds for the athletes to prepare for the games?\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For seasoned athletics reporter, Cece Omorogbe, the country would need to do more in the area of preparation and welfare.\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We must learn the right thing to achieve the best result.\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Take the case of Udodi Onwuzurike as an example, this guy won the men's 200m title at the World U-20 Championship three years ago in Nairobi, Kenya.\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 2117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2102, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"score\": 0.9999999984238457, \"rank\": 1.576226709400577e-09, \"text\": \"Nairobi\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\"}, {\"begin\": 2111, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9853361705160836, \"rank\": 0.014872947327379132, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Onwuzurike beat Botswana's Letsile Tebogo to second position at the competition.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2136, \"end\": 2144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.8678116594587586, \"rank\": 0.15232376645384182, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fast track to three years, Onwuzurike failed to make it to the final in Paris and Tebogo won the gold medal in the men's 200m.\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2273, \"end\": 2278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998908606, \"rank\": 1.0931179370576646e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The difference here is the support the two athletes received from their countries.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Most Nigeria's foreign-based athletes engage in part-time jobs abroad which hamper their development and performance.\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998226030742, \"rank\": 1.773969165549162e-07, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As an athlete, you need total concentration, not combining it with another job.\\\"\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Atlanta '96 women's long jump gold medalist, Chioma Ajunwa also corroborated Omorogbe's view.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chioma_Ajunwa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chioma Ajunwa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chioma_Ajunwa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chioma_Ajunwa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To win an Olympic medal is not an easy thing.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Every country comes to the Olympics with the aim of winning gold,\\\" Ajunwa said.\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For you to prepare, they give you four years.\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not something you can achieve in six months or three months.\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Athletes are preparing on their own.\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 2989, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's like going to training and deciding to press your phone instead of focusing on your workout.\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When athletes train alone, they relax when tired, but with coaches, they are motivated to push through.\\\"\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Way forward  It's back to the drawing board for Nigeria and the focus now should be to have a better outing at the next edition of the Olympics to be hosted in Los Angeles, United States of America.\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998226030742, \"rank\": 1.773969165549162e-07, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}, {\"begin\": 3356, \"end\": 3367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999999996958195, \"rank\": 2.887523936271804e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Charles Ogundiya, an award winning journalist believes the country needs to invest more in sports to have different results in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 3396, \"to\": 3535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3396, \"end\": 3403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6743382149177158, \"rank\": 0.47754897914551153, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 3523, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999999996958195, \"rank\": 2.887523936271804e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no need to dwell in the past, we can not change the result from Paris.\", \"from\": 3537, \"to\": 3617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3611, \"end\": 3616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998908606, \"rank\": 1.0931179370576646e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The focus now should be on how to get a better result at the next Olympics.\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The blame game will not solve anything.\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some countries use like eight years to prepare for an Olympics.\", \"from\": 3736, \"to\": 3799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The minimum you can do is four years.\", \"from\": 3800, \"to\": 3837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Aside from that, funds must be made available for the athletes and also the right facilities.\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These athletes pay nutritionists, coaches and do all other necessary things.\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 4012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There must be a proper plan and not the fire brigade approach we always adopt.\", \"from\": 4013, \"to\": 4091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There must also be continuity in the one we do.\", \"from\": 4093, \"to\": 4141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sports ministers must follow the laid down plans of their predecessors.\", \"from\": 4142, \"to\": 4217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea of always starting all over again will not help the country,\\\" he stated.\", \"from\": 4218, \"to\": 4299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Omorogbe has a different view on the way forward.\", \"from\": 4301, \"to\": 4350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He had this to say: \\\"It's important for us to start preparing here in Nigeria and make use of our own coaches.\", \"from\": 4352, \"to\": 4462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4422, \"end\": 4429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998226030742, \"rank\": 1.773969165549162e-07, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We used to have a high performance centre in Port Harcourt but I doubt if it is still functioning.\", \"from\": 4464, \"to\": 4563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4510, \"end\": 4523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Harcourt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.606988651148754e-26, \"text\": \"Port Harcourt\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Harcourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Harcourt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Let us work on our facilities here, not embark on a fruitless training tour in a few months to the start of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4565, \"to\": 4687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone once said a foreign coach will never train you to beat his country's athlete.\", \"from\": 4688, \"to\": 4773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The welfare of the athletes is very important.\", \"from\": 4775, \"to\": 4822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The government must do more in this area as well as the private sector.\", \"from\": 4823, \"to\": 4894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if you are the best, you still need that extra motivation to stay at the top.\\\"\", \"from\": 4895, \"to\": 4978, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tinubu in charge for eight years - Atiku's ex-aide, Bwala blasts critics  Noise pollution: Churches, clubs get 90-day ultimatum in Enugu  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Paris 2024 Olympics: Reuben launches Nigeria's final search for medal  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\", \"from\": 4980, \"to\": 5599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5438, \"end\": 5445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998226030742, \"rank\": 1.773969165549162e-07, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}, {\"begin\": 5464, \"end\": 5470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_and_Simon_Reuben\", \"score\": 0.945619132027193, \"rank\": 0.05642155587636328, \"text\": \"Reuben\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_and_Simon_Reuben\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_and_Simon_Reuben\"}, {\"begin\": 5534, \"end\": 5541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998226030742, \"rank\": 1.773969165549162e-07, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}]}"